question_title: Will the interest in “uf” change between 2026-02-02 and 2026-02-10 according to Google Trends?
summary: The search term "uf" primarily refers to the University of Florida. The Florida Gators are the defending 2025 NCAA basketball national champions, currently ranked #19 and leading the SEC. Key to this forecast: there's a basketball game on Feb 10 (at Georgia) but no major event on Feb 2 (the comparison date). This asymmetry suggests slight upward pressure on interest by Feb 10. However, regular season basketball games typically don't cause dramatic search spikes, and the ±3 threshold allows for substantial normal variation. I assign moderate probability to "Doesn't change" (45%) as the most likely outcome, with "Increases" (30%) slightly more likely than "Decreases" (25%) due to the game day effect on Feb 10.

factors.description: Basketball game on Feb 10 (at Georgia) but no game on Feb 2 - game days typically see elevated searches for team/school abbreviations
Defending national champions with elevated media attention and fan interest throughout 2025-26 season
University abbreviation search terms tend to be relatively stable week-to-week without major catalysts
The ±3 threshold on value of 49 (about 6% variation) captures substantial normal day-to-day fluctuation
Google Trends sampling variability adds noise - values can shift by several points between queries
